premise_source_doc_sentence: The Romani people are also known by a variety of other names ; in English as gypsies or gipsies  (  seen by some as a slur , as discussed below  )  and Roma , in Greek as γύφτοι  (  gífti  )  or τσιγγάνοι  (  tsingánoi  )  , in Central and Eastern Europe as Tsingani  (  and variants  )  , in France as gitans besides the dated bohémiens , manouches , in Italy as zingari and gitani , and in Spain as gitanos .
